accessibility.text: When the Fed sells bonds (QT) it disappears money by reducing bank reserves
When the Fed sells bonds (QT) it disappears money by reducing bank reserves
When the Fed sells 20b in bonds, it disappears 20b in reserves: ΔR = -20b
When the Fed sells bonds (QT) it disappears money by reducing bank reserves
Banks now have less than required reserves. As loans are paid back, instead of issuing new loans banks put the money paid into reserves: This means that the amount of loans outstanding decrease
